cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with a computer vision problem of partial domain adaptation, which involves transferring knowledge from a source domain to a target domain with a subset of classes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel approach that combines reinforcement learning and domain adaptation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as word embeddings, which could potentially place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which could place it under cs.MM (Multimedia).
